\f0\fs24 \cf0 Kubernetes is a portable, extensible platform for managing containerized services and workloads.\
Portable- read and writes its configuration settings into an accessible folder in the computer, usually the folder where the portable application can be found.\
Facilitiates declarative configurations and automation.\
\
\
When Kubernetes is deployed, one gets a cluster. A cluster contains a set of worker machines called nodes to run containeried applications.\
\
Helps manage containerised applications in different deployment environments.\
\
KUBERNETES ARCHITECTURE\
\
Cluster is made up of one master node\
     Node is a virtual or physical machine \
    Master ndode is connected to a couple of worker nodes where each node has a kubelet process running in it.\
Kubelet is a kubernetes process that makes it for the cluster to communicate to each other and execute tasks in the nodes like running the application processes\
\
