\f1\b \cf6 Volume\

\f0\b0 \cf4 Attaches a physical storage on a hard rive to your pod, this storage could be on a locally machine on the same server node where the pod is running or on a remote storage outside the kubernetes cluster e.g cloud storage that is not part of the cabernets cluster. You then reference this.\
\

\f1\b\fs26 \cf6 Deployment and StatefulSet\

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf4 Is a blueprint for the applications.\
Database can\'92t be replicated with deployment. Instead shouldd be replicated with stageful set.\
\

\fs26 \cf6 KUBERNETES CONFIGURATION
\fs24 \cf4 \
All configuration in kubernetes cluster goes through a master node in the process known as API Server.\
kUBERENETES CLIENTS talk to the API server and send their configuration requests to the API server.\
The requests are in yaml or json format. For example making a request to the cluster to configure a component called deployment(blueprint for creating pods)\
\
Each configuration file has 3 pats, :\
      Metadata\
      Specification\
      Status\
